    • level

      public LogAssertionsUtil.LogAssertion.LogAssertionBuilder level(Level level)
      Sets the expected log level of the log event.

      This method will convert the provided log level to a Log4j Level.

      Only the standard log levels are supported. If a custom log level is provided, it will be converted to the closest standard log level.

      Parameters:
      level - The log level to set.
      Returns:
      This builder.

    • position

      public LogAssertionsUtil.LogAssertion.LogAssertionBuilder position(@Nullable @Nullable Integer position)
      The position of the log event to check. 0 means the first (oldest) log event, 1 means the second, etc.

      If the position is negative, the position will be relative to the end of the log events. For example, -1 will get the last log event, -2 will get the second to last, etc.

      When null, all log events will be checked until the first one that matches the conditions.

      Default: null

      Returns:
      this.
